properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 5 at 2:44AM EST until February 6 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 20 to 25 kt and
seas 5 to 7 feet expected. For the Gale Watch, southwest winds 25
kt with frequent gusts up to 40 kt and seas 6 to 11 feet
possible.

* WHERE...Gulf waters from the Walton-Okaloosa County line to
the Ochlockonee River out 60 nautical miles.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, from 7 PM EST /6 PM CST/
this evening to 7 AM EST /6 AM CST/ Thursday. For the Gale
Watch, from Thursday morning through late Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.
